  "text": "The results of this study confirm that the ICQ-P, which was originally developed for adult patients with a chronic disease, is suitable for assessing the cognitions of the parents of a child recently diagnosed with cancer. The same three-factor (each with 6 items) structure of the original ICQ (Helplessness, Acceptance, Perceived Benefits) was also found in two samples of parents of children recently diagnosed with cancer. Factor loadings were adequate and exceeded previously determined factor loadings, showing that the adapted ICQ (ICQ-P) had an adequate factor structure. All subscales showed high reliability (α=.80-.88), comparable to that of the original questionnaire [CITATION_1] . Correlation analysis of the subscales of the ICQ-P demonstrated no association between Helplessness and Perceived Benefits, a small association between Acceptance and Perceived Benefits, and a moderate association between Helplessness and Acceptance, indicating that these factors are distinct constructs of illness cognitions.",
  "correct_citation": {
